            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-59730-ffmpeg",
              "name": "StockMatcherCpeMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-59730 medium vulnerability for ffmpeg package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When decoding a frame for a SANM file (ANIM v0 variant), the decoded data can be larger than the buffer allocated for it.\n\nFrames encoded with codec 48 can specify their resolution (width x height). A buffer of appropriate size is allocated depending on the resolution.\n\nThis codec can encode the frame contents using a run-length encoding algorithm. There are no checks that the decoded frame fits in the allocated buffer, leading to a heap-buffer-overflow.\n\nprocess_frame_obj initializes the buffers based on the frame resolution:\n\n\n\nWe recommend upgrading to version 8.0 or beyond."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-59730\nSeverity: medium\nPackage: ffmpeg\nVersion: 7.1.1\nFix Version: 8.0\nType: binary\nLocation: /tavus-pipecat-example/env/lib/python3.13/site-packages/cv2/.dylibs/libavcodec.61.19.101.dylib\nData Namespace: nvd:cpe\nLink: [CVE-2025-59730](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-59730)",
