            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-69693-ffmpeg",
              "name": "StockMatcherCpeMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-69693 medium vulnerability for ffmpeg package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Out-of-bounds read in FFmpeg 8.0 and 8.0.1 RV60 video decoder (libavcodec/rv60dec.c). The quantization parameter (qp) validation at line 2267 only checks the lower bound (qp \u003c 0) but is missing upper bound validation. The qp value can reach 65 (base value 63 from 6-bit frame header + offset +2 from read_qp_offset) while the rv60_qp_to_idx array has size 64 (valid indices 0-63). This results in out-of-bounds array access at lines 1554 (decode_cbp8), 1655 (decode_cbp16), and 1419/1421 (get_c4x4_set), potentially leading to memory disclosure or crash. A previous fix in commit 61cbcaf93f added validation only for intra frames. This vulnerability affects the released versions 8.0 (released 2025-08-22) and 8.0.1 (released 2025-11-20) and is fixed in git master commit 8abeb879df which will be included in FFmpeg 8.1."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-69693\nSeverity: medium\nPackage: ffmpeg\nVersion: 8.0.1\nFix Version: \nType: binary\nLocation: /tavus-pipecat-example/env/lib/python3.13/site-packages/av/.dylibs/libavcodec.62.11.100.dylib\nData Namespace: nvd:cpe\nLink: [CVE-2025-69693](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-69693)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-69693**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| medium  | ffmpeg  | 8.0.1  |   | binary  | /tavus-pipecat-example/env/lib/python3.13/site-packages/av/.dylibs/libavcodec.62.11.100.dylib  | nvd:cpe  | [CVE-2025-69693](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-69693)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:generic/ffmpeg@8.0.1"
                ],
                "security-severity": "5.4"
              }
            },
